125. Deductions which may be made from wages
: (1) No deduction shall be made from the
wages of a worker except those authorised by or under this Act.
(2) Deductions from the wages of a worker shall be made only in accordance with the
provisions of this Act, and may be of the following kinds only, namely—
(a) fines imposed under section 25 ;
(b) deductions for absence from duty ;
